#### What is the expected behavior?
CdkStep stepControl is of type AbstractControl as defined in the documentation

#### What is the current behavior?
When looking at the type definitions for CdkStep stepControl is as defined as follows:
 stepControl: {
        valid: boolean;
        invalid: boolean;
        pending: boolean;
        reset: () => void;
    };

#### What are the steps to reproduce?
Install Material/CDK 7.3.4. Try to use stepControl get function it will fail with the following typescript error:

 TS2339: Property 'get' does not exist on type '{ valid: boolean; invalid:
boolean; pending: boolean; reset: () => void; }'.


#### Which versions of Angular, Material, OS, TypeScript, browsers are affected?
Angular 7.2.9
Material 7.3.4
CDK 7.3.4
Typescript 3.1.6

#### Is there anything else we should know?
Downgrading to Material/CDK 7.3.2 fixes the issue

#### What is the expected behavior?
In all other browsers when i monitor an element via:
```typescript
  ngAfterViewInit() {
    this._focusMonitor
      .monitor(this.elementRef, true)
//      .pipe(debounceTime(0))
      .subscribe(focusOrigin => {
        if (!focusOrigin && this.radioGroup) {
          this.radioGroup._touch();
        }
      });
  }
```

And i click on the element, 2 values get emitted with `focusOrigin === 'mouse'`.

The workaround i've found is to add a `debounceTime(0)` like the commented line above.

The code in question is from `radio.ts` in material.

#### What is the current behavior?
On IE11, between the `'mouse'` values, i get a `null` value emitted.

#### What are the steps to reproduce?
Try running the example https://stackblitz.com/angular/kgnogyvppxp?file=app%2Fform-field-label-example.ts on IE11 and a console.log in `radio.ts` on the `focusOrigin`.

#### Which versions of Angular, Material, OS, TypeScript, browsers are affected?
Latest material, IE11.
